TZ=America/Chicago

# HOST CPU NOTE
#
# Dockhand's collection-worker queries the Docker stats API per container
# (/containers/{id}/stats) and aggregates them. It cannot see non-Docker
# processes (Unraid OS, SMB, ZFS, etc.), so the CPU reading reflects
# "total CPU used by Docker containers" — not true host CPU utilization.
#
# Adding /:/host:ro and HOST_PROC=/host/proc does NOT help — the Go binary
# has no code that reads those paths; it is purely Docker API based.
#
# For accurate host CPU, use beszel-agent (it mounts /:/host:ro and reads
# /proc/stat directly).
